<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Phase 24.2e (ADR-017 §3.5) — Apple Push Notification service.

        `aps-environment` value = "production":
            TestFlight builds use the production APNs gateway even though
            they are pre-release. The "development" value applies only to
            debugger-attached local builds (Xcode → Run on device with
            development provisioning profile). Hardcoding "production"
            here matches the closed-beta TestFlight distribution path.
            Local debugger push test is deferred to Phase 24.4+ if real
            demand surfaces (would require a Configuration-conditional
            xcconfig switch + per-config entitlements path).

        Capability: ensure the App ID `io.github.b150005.skeinly`
        registered in Apple Developer Portal has the "Push Notifications"
        capability enabled, AND the Distribution Provisioning Profile
        embedded in the IPA includes that capability. Both must align
        with this entitlement value or `xcodebuild` reports a code-sign
        mismatch at archive time.

        **On-device debug push test is unsupported by design**: a
        debug-signed local build on a physical device using the
        development APNs gateway (`api.development.push.apple.com`)
        will fail registration here with "No valid 'aps-environment'
        entitlement string found" — the failure is handled gracefully
        (nil token, 30s timeout) so there is no crash, but the token
        callback will never fire. Tester push QA happens via TestFlight
        only. Phase 24.4+ may revisit if a local-debug push iteration
        path becomes necessary (would require xcconfig-conditional
        APS_ENVIRONMENT + per-config entitlements paths).
    -->
    <key>aps-environment</key>
    <string>production</string>
</dict>
</plist>
